CHAT.comment: Everyone in the family talks quite a bit , except for the father who barely says anything. I noticed a few key times when Chi starts talking to her Mother , who interrupts her to talk about something else. Bro is very energetic , he's constantly moving around , singing , and quoting TV characters and commercials. The family discusses getting a Himalayan cat (they already have six) and volunteering or working at an animal shelter. Chi is involved in many extracurriculars , including gymnastics and a singing group. They stay on topic longer than most , and the children (Chi's age and older) seem to get along relatively well. Tape lasts about 18 minutes but MT may have been longer since the tape cuts in and out sometimes. Chi tells about bumping her head at gymnastics and ends <so that's the end of my gymnastics story>
